  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large tagine pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the black cardamom pods and lemongrass stalks to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken thighs to the pot and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-6 minutes.",
    "Add the lemongrass paste, lemongrass honey, and white wine vinegar to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer the tagine for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Stir in chopped parsley and serve the tagine hot over couscous or rice.",
    "Garnish with additional lemongrass stalks and parsley, if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
